column5: WTG Shawn!!    That is a sweet surprise for this time of the year.  Congrats

Funny looking laker for sure!  Congrats on a real beauty FD.
A fish of a life time there. Amazing walleye!
great eye man congrats
HOLY COW!!!!      that's a pig, great catch  peps
Great looking walleye, nice colors!!!
Congrats with the PB and making the wall of fame at the resort!! Thanks for the report and pics are wicked!!  Cheers, 1leg
Great fish, now if everyone would do the same as you. Take your picture and weight and let her go to keep on making big fish!! Great job Shawn Scooter
nice fish a bonus for the team wish i could get out sometime soon
Beauty eye for sure!  Amazing what can come from that CLEAR water...
Wicked fish fishindevil, how many hooks were you seeing down there? Maybe you found the "Motherlode" I wish everyone would live release beautiful breeders like that one. Congrats.  Stan
Uh Shawn... DAUM!!!!!!!
WWWWOOOOOWWWWW!!!!!!!!!  Nice one!  Did you go back out to that spot to try for more later on in your trip????  I mean...walleye tend to congregate in the same size range, don't they?
Great fish Shawn. Congrats and keep the reports coming.  Mike

I Was camping up north a couple of weeks ago and of course doing some walleye fishing,and doing quite well with lots of smaller 14-17inch fish being caught,and a few smallies and even a few small 25inch pike to boot,when i was seeing a few big hooks on my lowrance off a deep drop going from 22ft of water and within a few feet it drops down to almost 50ft of water,well i made a few passes along the drop,and around the 42ft mark there was a few big hooks ,so i thought they might be lake trout as they are in this lake,so i was using one of my homemade floating worm harnesses,and a 2oz bottom bouncer,with a big dew worm,and i trolled it along the drop one last time,and band "FISH-ON  !!!!  well after a few mins i was really feeling the big head shakes,and short drag pulling runs that can only be yup...walleye !!!! well up she came to the surface,and i knew she was a good size fish but,man i was suprised to see a huge walleye,so i netted her really quick,and precise..and loaded her into the livewell,and made the 6 mile run back to the campsite/resort,where i could get her weighed,and mesured,so i could release her unharmed...well they were all shocked as there has not been a walleye caught that they know of for over 20yrs,and thats how long ago they were stocked in that lake...so they took pictures of me & my fish and put the pictures at the front of the resort wall for everyone to see,she was weighed on official toledo scales as they have pike & bass derbies for the resort on the lake,so she was official at 10.3/4 lbs 33"inches long and was released to be caught another day,so we do know that the fish is 20yrs old,she was a blast to catch so here are the pics,oh ya and this one is for our team catch 22 !!!!ya baby          and the release shot !!!!    and here are a few more pictures from the place were at enjoy!!!!!!!
Ya gotta love fishing, because you never know what could happen, and what surprise might be at the end of your line. Great catch by the way.
